Extraction, Transformation and Load Basics

EXTRACT TRANSFORM AND LOAD DATA USING SSIS

Using Visual Studio, we will Extract the 3 .xls files, transform them and load to SQL Server Management.            

   1. Open Microsoft Visual Studio from your start menu.

       

         2. Click on New Project

        

       3. Click on Integration Services and give your Project a meaningful name. 

           

       4.  Right Click on SSIS Packages and Click on New SSIS Package.

                

     5. Give you package a meaningful name. 

        

       6. Once a package has been created, drag and drop a data flow task in the control flow.

7.  Double Click on Data flow task to switch to the Data flow tab. Drag and drop an Excel Source on data flow             canvas.

   

8. Download the attached folder, save it in your computer in desired location and exact it to unzip the folder.     

 

               

       9. Double click on Excel source to launch the Excel Source Editor dialog box. In the Excel Source Editor dialog            box, click New which will open Excel Connection Manager. 

      10. In the Excel Connection Manager dialog box, click Browse, and then provide your excel file path                             (select Accounts.xls file from your folder). Confirm that Microsoft Excel 97-2003 is selected in the Excel Version       box and then click OK.   

        

        

     11. In the Excel Source Editor dialog box, select accounts$ in the Name of the Excel Sheet list box.

       

        12. Click OK to close the Excel Source Editor. Give your Excel Connection Manager a meaningful name (i.e.                   Accounts).

         

     13. Double Click on Excel Source for Configuration and check all the columns. Click Ok.

            

         14.  Drag and drop a Data conversion transformation to convert data from unicode to non-unicode format. Connect            the data path from Excel Source to Data Conversion Transformation.

        

        15. Double Click on Data conversion transformation task, check all the columns and change the data type from           Unicode to Non-unicode (i.e. String) format. Click Ok. 

           

        

        16. Drag and Drop an OLE DB Destination on the data flow canvas. Double Click on the OLEDB Destination                 to create a connection manager.

        

        

            17. Once a connection manager has been created, click new to create the table dbo. Account to load data in                  previously created database and click ok.

    

        18. Click on Mappings to Map the converted input column with the Destination column. Click Ok.

        

        

        19. In the control flow drag and drop two data flow tasks to configure two more tables and repeat the same                    process for two tables i.e.Users and Revenue_Invoice_Info. Put all the data flow task into the Sequence                  Container, then execute the package to load the data from the Excel source into SQL server.

             

        20. Return to the SSMS and check under database if the three tables have been loaded. The table                                Users, Accounts, revenue_invoice_info are already loaded in our database as shown in the image below.
